      <abstract audience="internal" id="aspace_8d4b0f6af460a047d246ff4686ce4549">The Henry Smals
        Diaries, 1871-1891, consist of three boxes containing eighteen volumes of diaries written by
        Henry Smals of Bridgewater, Virginia. The topics of diary entries are brief outlining
        day-to-day activities. A folder, located in Box 3, contains a partial index and a list of
        highlights for most volumes as well as an ad for "Henry Smals, Fashionable Barber! Main
        Street, Bridgewater, Va."</abstract>
    </did>
