      <custodhist audience="internal" id="aspace_ea3cbd175f70943c3fb9f5120a96428c">
        <head>Provenance</head>
        <p>The collection of diaries was first presented to George M. Hanger by Smals' grandson, Gal
          Miller, in 1910. The diaries were then given to George P. Furry in 1920, Edwina Furry in
          1970, and Dorothy Merriefield in 1983.</p>
      </custodhist>
      <processinfo audience="internal" id="aspace_5a059cba61fbc634ac068de6f45c896c">
        <head>Processing Notes</head>
        <p>The diaries appear to have been rebound, perhaps several times, and some volumes have
          sections in them that are not in chronological order. In some places the ink has faded to
          illegibility. In order to streamline the process of applying collection numbers, Special
          Collections staff completed a large-scale renumbering campaign in the spring of 2017.
            <emph render="bold">This collection was previously cataloged as SC 2059</emph>.</p>
      </processinfo>
