    <bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_51f5ebe15258069b73b7872e643966a1">
      <head>Biographical Information</head>
      <p>Henry Smals (1810-1892) is listed in the 1850 Rockingham County Census as a shoemaker with
        real estate value of $1,000 with a wife, Mary, and six children. There is an entry for Henry
        Smalts in the 1860 census and for Henry Smalls in the 1870 census that gives additional
        household details. He may also have been a barber sometime during the 1880s (ses Box 3,
        Folder 4). His surname appears as a variation of Smalz and Smaltz as well.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_cf7ebbcbca6711847115dbdb3da1f1a2">
      <head>Scope and Content</head>
      <p>The Henry Smals Diaries, 1871-1891, consist of three boxes containing eighteen volumes of
        diaries written by Henry Smals of Bridgewater, Virginia. The topics of diary entries are
        brief outlining day-to-day activities. There are mentions of acquaintances that are ill,
        various business transactions conducted in town, the movement of livestock, and hay through
        town, ongoing town projects, churcch activities, marriages, births, deaths, and other
        details of town life. The activities of "colored people" are occasionally noted. Throughout
        the diaries, Smals made small drawings of people and animals and added illustrations
        cclipped from newspapers. A folder, located in Box 3, contains printed copies of a <extref
          xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple"
          xlink:href="http://www.lib.jmu.edu/special/manuscripts/Smals_Index_Hinkle.aspx">partial
          index</extref> and a <extref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
          xlink:type="simple"
          xlink:href="http://www.lib.jmu.edu/special/manuscripts/Smals_highlights_Dillard.aspx">list
          of highlights</extref> for most columes as well as an ad for "Henry Smals, Fashionable
        Barber! Main Street, Bridgewater, Va."</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement audience="internal" id="aspace_a02db0f9914aa49aefd45792fe87856a">
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>The diaries are arranged chronologically where possible, but due to variations in size are
        physically housed as follows in the Contents List. Volume 14 is filed in a separate
        container.</p>
    </arrangement>
